      <div xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412">
        <head xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-Hd1e99" type="question-title">De constantia</head>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-d1e102">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e22412-Qd1e112" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-Rd1e104">Gregorius, in
              <title>Homiliis</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-Qd1e112">Non nos prospera elevent, non adversa
              perturbent: ut qui in soliditate fidei figimur, nequaquam rerum transeuntium
              mutabilitate moveamur.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-d1e117">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e22412-Qd1e127" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-Rd1e119">Gregorius, in
              <title>Moralibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-Qd1e127">Sancti viri nec sustinere falsa per infirmitatem
              metuunt, nec laesi unquam a veritate conticescunt.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-d1e132">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e22412-Qd1e142" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-Rd1e134">Gregorius, in
              <title>Moralibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-Qd1e142">Electi ipsa, quae fortiter tolerant, supplicia
              perhorrescunt, ita ut in eis uno eodemque tempore, et constantia ex virtute sit, et
              pavor ex carne.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-d1e147">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e22412-Qd1e157" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-Rd1e149">Gregorius, in
              <title>Moralibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-Qd1e157">Justi viri securitas recte leoni comparatur,
              quia cum contra se quoslibet insurgere conspicit, ad mentis suae constantiam redit; et
              scit quia cunctos adversantes superat, quia illum solum diligit, quem invitus nullo
              modo amittit.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-d1e163">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e22412-Qd1e173" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-Rd1e165">Gregorius, in
              <title>Moralibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-Qd1e173">Vir sanctus, quo majore persecutione premitur,
              eo ad praedicandum veritatem acrius instigatur: et cum constanter persecutores
              tolerat, ardenter ad se auditores trahere festinat.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-d1e178">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e22412-Qd1e188" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-Rd1e180">Gregorius, in
              <title>Moralibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-Qd1e188">Si semel in appetitu supernae patriae forti
              stabilitate animus figitur, minus rerum temporalium perturbatione vexatur.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-d1e193">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e22412-Qd1e203" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-Rd1e195">Gregorius,
              <title>super Ezechielem</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-Qd1e203">Timeri ab omnibus homo debuerat, si ipse
              auctorem omnium, ut homo, timuisset. Nam qui rationis sensum ad timorem Dei non habet,
              tanto in nullo timendus est, quanto hoc, quod ipse esse debuit, non est.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-d1e208">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e22412-Qd1e218" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-Rd1e210">Gregorius, in
              <title>Registro</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-Qd1e218">Hoc certissime scito, quod placere Deo, et
              pravis hominibus nullus potest. In tantum ergo se existimet fraternitas tua
              omnipotenti Deo placuisse, quanto se perversis hominibus displicuisse
              cognoverit.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-d1e223">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e22412-Qd1e233" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-Rd1e225">Augustinus, in
              <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-Qd1e233">Senti de Augustino quidquid libet; sola me in
              oculis Dei conscientia non accuset.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-d1e238">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e22412-Qd1e248" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-Rd1e240">Augustinus,
              <title>de Civitate Dei</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-Qd1e248"
              source="http://scta.info/resource/adcd-l5-d1e812">Virtutes habenti, magna virtus est
              contemnere gloriam.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-d1e254">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e22412-Qd1e264" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-Rd1e256">Augustinus,
              <title>de Civitate Dei</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-Qd1e264"
              source="http://scta.info/resource/adcd-l5-d1e812">Qui contemnit judicia laudantium,
              contemnit etiam suspicantium temeritatem: quorum tamen, si vere bonus est, non
              contemnit salutem.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-d1e269">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e22412-Qd1e279" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-Rd1e271">Augustinus, in
              <title>Sermonibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-Qd1e279">Nec valde gaudere debemus quando laudamur, nec
              contristari quando vituperamur, quia nec damnare injuria, nec coronare potest laus
              falsa.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-d1e284">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e22412-Qd1e294" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-Rd1e286">Ambrosius,
              <title>de Officiis</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-Qd1e294">Bene sibi conscius, falsis non debet moveri; nec
              aestimari plus ponderis in alieno esse convitio, quam in suo testimonio.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-d1e299">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e22412-Qd1e309" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-Rd1e301">Joannes
            Chrysostomus, in <title>Sermone</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-Qd1e309">Quidquid erroris habet mundus, contemno:
              quidquid delectabile habet, rideo: divitias non cupio, paupertatem non horresco,
              mortem non timeo.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-d1e314">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e22412-Qd1e324" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-Rd1e316">Hieronymus, in
              <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-Qd1e324">Utinam, ob Dei mei nomen atque justitiam,
              universa me infidelium turba persequatur et tribulet: utinam in opprobrium meum
              solidus exurgat hic mundus: tantum ut a Christo merear laudari, et suae
              pollicitationis sperare mercedem.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-d1e329">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e22412-Qd1e339" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-Rd1e331">Hieronymus, in
              <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-Qd1e339">Gratias ago Deo meo, quod dignus sum habitus,
              quem mundus oderit.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-d1e345">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e22412-Qd1e355" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-Rd1e347">Hieronymus, in
              <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-Qd1e355">Per bonam et malam famam, a dextris et a
              sinistris, Christi miles graditur; nec laude extollitur, nec vituperatione frangitur;
              non divitiis tumet, non confunditur paupertate, et laeta contemnit, et
              tristia.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-d1e360">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e22412-Qd1e370" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-Rd1e362">Hieronymus, in
              <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-Qd1e370">Nec affectamus laudes hominum, nec
              vituperationes expavescimus: Deo enim placere curantes, minas hominum penitus non
              timemus, quoniam dissipat Deus ossa eorum, qui hominibus placere desiderant.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-d1e375">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e22412-Qd1e385" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-Rd1e377">Seneca, in
              <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-Qd1e385">Honores et injuriae vulgi in promiscuo sunt
              habendae; nec his gaudendum, nec illis dolendum.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-d1e390">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e22412-Qd1e400" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-Rd1e392">Seneca, in
              <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-Qd1e400">Animum excellentem, constantem et moderatum, et
              omnia tanquam se minora transeuntem, quidquid timemus optamusque ridentem, coelestis
              potentia agitat. Non potest res tanta sine adminiculo numinis stare.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-d1e405">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e22412-Qd1e415" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-Rd1e407">Seneca, in
              <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-Qd1e415">Vir bonus, quod honeste se facturum putaverit,
              faciet, etiamsi laboriosum erit; faciet, etiamsi periculosum erit. Rursum quod turpe
              erit non faciet, etiamsi pecuniam afferret, etiamsi voluptatem, etiamsi potentiam et
              dignitatem: ab honesto nulla re deterrebitur, ad turpia nulla re invitabitur.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-d1e420">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e22412-Qd1e430" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-Rd1e422">Seneca, in
              <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e22412-Qd1e430">Aequo animo audienda sunt imperitorum convicia,
              et ad honesta vadenti contemnendus est ipse contemptus.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
      </div>
